import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'] = pd.to_numeric(data['miles'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='gas_per_mile', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas_per_mile'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average gas per mile')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per mile?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='gas_per_mile', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['gas_per_mile'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
